  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Pacific Resilience Project Phase II (PREP II)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the face of increasingly intense extreme weather disturbances and hazards, the Republic of the Marshall Islands (RMI) requires greater investment in disaster risk reduction and mitigation efforts. The proposed Community Disaster Risk Management and Emergency Communications Training (CDRM-ECT) project is a small component of the larger World Bank Pacific Resilience Project &#x2013; Phase II (PREP II) currently being implemented in the RMI. Through this project, IOM is contributing to enhancing the overall capacity of the communities and governments of RMI to be better prepared for, and more resilient to hazard events and disasters by equipping community members to have increased capacity to manage disasters, increasing the capacity of communities to implement emergency communications protocols through the use of upgraded emergency communications equipment and skills, and increasing opportunities for disaster risk management and emergency communications professionals in RMI through localized training certification options.</narrative>
  </description>
